Example 29

Write as a ratio, without simplifying your answer:
(a) Jack has $\$5$ and Jill has 50 cents.
(b) Mix 200 mL of cordial with 1 L of water.

Solutions:

(a) Jack : Jill $= \$5 : 50$ cents {write in the correct order}
$= 500$ cents $: 50$ cents {write in the same units}
$= 500 : 50$ {express without units}

(b) cordial : water $= 200$ mL $: 1$ L {write in the correct order}
$= 200$ mL $: 1000$ mL {write in the same units}
$= 200 : 1000$ {express without units}
